    <briefdescription>
<para>This class allows to extract content from the .pdf documents of any kind. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>PDF documents can have a textual layer (copyable documents) or be without it (images, scanned documents).</para>
<para>:class:<computeroutput>~dedoc.readers.PdfAutoReader</computeroutput> is used for automatic detection of a correct textual layer in the given PDF file:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>if PDF document has a correct textual layer then :class:<computeroutput>~dedoc.readers.PdfTxtlayerReader</computeroutput> or :class:<computeroutput>~dedoc.readers.PdfTabbyReader</computeroutput> is used \ for document content extraction;</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>if PDF document doesn&apos;t have a correct textual layer then :class:<computeroutput>~dedoc.readers.PdfImageReader</computeroutput> is used for document content extraction.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>For more information, look to <computeroutput>pdf_with_text_layer</computeroutput> option description in :ref:<computeroutput>pdf_handling_parameters</computeroutput>. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
